## MCP
- `mcp/client.rs` — MCP client connection and tool discovery
- `mcp/protocol.rs` — MCP wire protocol types
- `mcp/config.rs` — MCP server configuration
- `mcp/mod.rs`

## ACP (Agent Communication Protocol / Zed)
- `acp/mod.rs` — GrokAdapter, session management, BacklocksMap
- `acp/protocol.rs` — SessionUpdateAction, ContextBlock, message types
- `acp/tools.rs` — tool definitions for ACP
- `acp/elicitation.rs` — user permission elicitation
- `acp/handlers.rs`
- `acp/mcp_bridge.rs` — bridge between ACP sessions and MCP servers
- `acp/slash_commands.rs` — built-in slash command handling (`/help`, `/rule`, `/commit`, etc.)
- `acp/security.rs` — path sandboxing for ACP
- `acp/status_bar.rs`

## Integration Points
- ACP tools route to `src/tools/`
- MCP tools are exposed as `server:tool_name` (e.g. `markmap:generate`)
- Slash commands feed into prompt / goal / rule systems

## Recent Changes
- Expanded MCP bridge support
- Rich slash command set including Bayesian and diagnostics
- Better security sandboxing

## Dependencies
- JSON-RPC style protocol for Zed ACP

## Notes
- ACP is the primary integration point for Zed editor.
- MCP allows external tool servers to be discovered and used dynamically.